    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just hard to see the \"hope\" in wrestling with this every single second. i look at people who are healthy and it feels like they're living in a completely different universe. i feel like i'm just a burden to everyone, too, because i'm always complaining or just stuck in a bad mood because of the agony. sometimes i feel like the most merciful thing would be to just let go, so everyone else can have their lives back and i can finally have some peace. do you think that's a selfish way to think? or is it just... logical?",
